%% RHOAI Operator (rhods-operator) - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Admin User
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as rhods-operator<br/>Controller Manager
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controller<br/>(e.g., KServe)
    participant Manifests as Kustomize Manifests<br/>/opt/manifests (local)

    Note over Admin,Manifests: Flow 1: Component Deployment

    Admin->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply DSCInitialization CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (kubeconfig)
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event: DSCI created
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create namespace, NetworkPolicies<br/>Configure Service Mesh, TrustedCA<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Operator-->>K8sAPI: DSCI status: Ready

    Admin->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply DataScienceCluster CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (kubeconfig)
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event: DSC created
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Component CRs<br/>(Dashboard, KServe, etc.)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>CompCtrl: Watch event: Component CR created
    CompCtrl->>Manifests: Load Kustomize manifests<br/>(local filesystem)
    Manifests-->>CompCtrl: Rendered manifests
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Deploy component resources<br/>(Deployments, Services, CRDs)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>CompCtrl: Resources created
    CompCtrl-->>K8sAPI: Component CR status: Ready

    Note over Admin,Manifests: Flow 2: KServe Model Inference (with Service Mesh)

    participant Client as External Client
    participant IstioGW as Istio Ingress Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>50051/TCP gRPC mTLS
    participant Predictor as KServe Predictor Pod<br/>8012/TCP HTTP mTLS
    participant Storage as Model Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Client->>IstioGW: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+ (SIMPLE)
    IstioGW->>Authorino: External AuthZ check<br/>gRPC/50051 mTLS
    Authorino-->>IstioGW: Auth decision
    IstioGW->>Predictor: Inference request<br/>HTTP/8012 mTLS (Istio sidecar)
    Predictor->>Storage: Load model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Storage credentials
    Storage-->>Predictor: Model artifacts
    Predictor-->>IstioGW: Prediction response
    IstioGW-->>Client: JSON response<br/>HTTPS

    Note over Admin,Manifests: Flow 3: Monitoring (Managed RHOAI)

    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS
    participant Alert as Alertmanager<br/>10443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OCPMon as OpenShift Monitoring
    participant User as User

    Prom->>CompCtrl: Scrape /metrics endpoints<br/>HTTP(S) various ports<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Prom->>Alert: Send alerts<br/>HTTPS/10443<br/>TLS (serving cert)
    OCPMon->>Prom: Federation scrape<br/>HTTPS/9091<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    User->>Prom: Access Prometheus Route<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS (reencrypt)<br/>Auth: OAuth proxy
